    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>+ In nomine domini Dei eterni. Anno ab incarnacione domini nostri Iesu
                        Christi millesimo e XX octavo, indicione VI. Nos <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Count #marriage #Ordinatio" ref="#people/3571"
                            >Albertus</persName> Dei gratia <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux,
                            marchio</rs> et <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> divina cooperante gratia et
                        beati Petri et domini <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs>
                        <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/3560">Honorii</persName> eius vicarii
                        munere ad huius honoris provectus fastigia sepe sepius memorie reducentes,
                        eterne beatitudinis premia et ecclesias in suo stato retinere et pauperibus
                        iustitias facere proposuimus divina favente clementia. Quare reverende in
                        Christo pater <persName key="#Abbots #Monasteries #Ordinatio"
                            ref="#people/3568">Henrice</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasteri</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Ordinatio" ref="#juridical_persons/2001"
                            >Sancti Benedicti iuxta Padum</orgName>, vestris precibus annuens, tum
                        pro Dei amore, tum pro domini pape dilectione, tum pro eiusdem sancti
                        monasterii religione, tum pro peccatorum meorum nostrorumque parentum
                        remissione, tum pro <rs key="#marriage">coniugis</rs> nostre petitione, tum
                        etiam et pro mercede anime domine <rs key="#Countess">comitisse</rs>
                        <persName key="#Countess" ref="#people/125">Matildis</persName>, <rs
                            key="#Ordinatio">volumus</rs> prefatum monasterium quecumque sibi vel a
                        prefata comitissa vel ab aliquo eius fideli vel ab alia quacumque persona,
                        magna vel parva usque nunc datum possidet, in re mobili vel immobili seu in
                        decimis, vel per se vel per hobedientias suas vel in scriptis suis habet,
                        firmum deinceps habere sine omni nostra nostrorumque heredum contradicione.
                        Insuper volumus ut si quis noster fidelis de <placeName ref="#places/4196"
                            >Padus</placeName> eiusdem comitisse a nobis in beneficio habens, sicut
                        mos est, eorum aliquid inde pro mercede anime sue eidem monasterio aut
                        hobedienciis eius dare voluerit, vel testamento relinquere, liberam habeat
                        potestatem, ita sane ut talem partem inde retineat ut nostrum servitium
                        facere ipse et sui heredes valeant. Et ut huius nostri scripti tenor firmum
                        in perpet*** credatur, et a nullo nostrorum heredum quod absit aliqua
                        occasione infrigatur, pena ab eo qui rem eiusdem monasterii molestaverit <rs
                            key="#Penalty">in duplum</rs> eidem ecclesie componi debere statuimus,
                        insuper hoc nostre concessionis scriptum manu propria corroborantes
                        fidelibus nostris ut idoneis <rs key="#Witness">testibus</rs> corroborandum
                        tradidimus. Signum manuum Albertus Dei gratia dux et marchio et comes, qui
                        hanc cartam scribere iussit. Signum manuum <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/2193">Sasso</persName> et <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/4012">Brogognone</persName> testes. Signum manuum <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/2194">Amedeus</persName> testis. Signum
                        manuum <persName key="#Witness #childOf" ref="#people/4003"
                            >Bernardinus</persName>
                        <rs key="#parentOf">filius</rs>
                        <persName key="parentOf" ref="#people/4004">Maleadubati</persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness">Wibertus Rufus</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Ardoinus">Arduinus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/4007">Enricus</persName> de
                        Bundeno, <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/4008">Wibertus</persName> et
                            <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/4009">Markise</persName> de
                        Castellarano, <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Cuneradus"
                            >Conradus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #childOf"
                            ref="#people/4014">Ugo</persName> de <persName key="parentOf"><name
                                ref="Petrus">Petrone</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/3517">Opizu</persName> de Gunzaga, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/4013">Ubertus</persName> de <placeName ref="#places/4413"
                            >Sancto Benedicto</placeName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rainerius">Rainerius</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #childOf" ref="#people/4015">Ugicion</persName> filii
                            <persName key="parentOf"><name ref="Albertus">Alberti</name></persName>
                        testes. Ego <persName key="#Notary #Writer #Ordinatio"><name ref="Albertus"
                                >Albertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> hanc cartam rogatus <rs key="#Writer"
                            >scripsi</rs>, post traditam complevi. </ab>
